// named.conf.example — ShadowDNS starter configuration
//
// Copy this file to your working directory and adjust the values in the
// included files below. ShadowDNS parses a BIND-compatible named.conf subset;
// see the project README for a full list of supported directives.
//
// This skeleton follows the Debian/Ubuntu BIND convention of splitting the
// configuration across three files:
//
//   - named.conf          — this file: only the two include directives below
//   - named.conf.options  — the global options{} (and logging{}) block
//   - named.conf.local    — the zone views
//
// Includes are resolved relative to this file's directory; adjust the paths
// if you store the included files elsewhere.

include "named.conf.options";
include "named.conf.local";
